parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become stuck in gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls while in park
the transmission fails to shift gears
or the vehicle jerks or makes a clunking noise when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's lights, radio, and other accessories to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: the radio does not turn on
interior lights do not come on
windshield wipers do not come on
hazard lights do not work when the engine is off
and the key gets stuck in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The electrical system makes clicking noises
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the electrical system to fail, leading to loss of power steering and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the doors lock and unlock randomly
the lights on the dashboard flash
and the air conditioning and heating systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the key to stick in the ignition lock cylinder, making it difficult or impossible to start the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key sticks in the ignition lock cylinder
and the emergency flasher lights do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to seize, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: and the anti-skid and ABS warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
